Visibly shaken on his way back to the corner, Garcia stayed on his stool as the bell for round nine rang. I knew he was hurt though.‚Äù\n \n‚ÄúWhen I got the shot to my head in the final round, that‚Äôs when I couldn‚Äôt see from my eye,‚Äù said Garcia, who owns the WBA Super Featherweight World Title. ‚ÄúI didn‚Äôt know where I was when he hit me with that shot. My vision is back but my head still hurts. I couldn‚Äôt see from my right eye. It was going well up until that point. I was picking my shots.‚Äù\n \nThe two champions jockeyed for position over the first three rounds before Davis got the fans back on their feet with a series of hard power shots late in round four. Garcia displayed a solid straight left hand that he employed to counter the speed of Davis‚Äô jabs, and was the busier fighter according to CompuBox, throwing 345 punches to Davis‚Äô 239.\n \nHowever, it was Davis‚Äô effective and efficient attack, which built as the fight went on, that helped him take control of the fight. After landing only four power punches in the first three rounds, Davis connected on 69 in rounds four through eight.\n \n‚ÄúI wasn‚Äôt throwing a lot of shots in the beginning because I was trying to beat him mentally,‚Äù said Davis. ‚ÄúI was trying to trick him with my hands and my eyes and things like that because he‚Äôs a tough fighter.
